                            <comment id="13243022" author="umamaheswararao" created="Sat, 31 Mar 2012 05:20:39 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;What is the final result of this voting?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I am thinking that, we should not access any non exposed APIs from HDFS at least from this version. We should bring the requirement of the usage and need of that APIs to HDFS. Get the access throw some public interfacing. So, that even though HDFS changes internal APIs, public interfacing would remains same. So, Hbase/Other dependant users need need end up in reflections for every version compatibility.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thoughts?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13243085" author="ram_krish" created="Sat, 31 Mar 2012 08:37:35 +0000"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;So, Hbase/Other dependant users need need end up in reflections for every version compatibility&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I think you meant need &apos;not&apos;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13243092" author="umamaheswararao" created="Sat, 31 Mar 2012 09:05:05 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yes, Ram. typo &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/smile.gif&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Here is what I meant:&lt;br/&gt;
We should not access any non exposed APIs from HDFS at least from this version. We should bring the requirement to HDFS about the usage and need of that APIs in Hbase. Get the access throw some public interfacing. So, that even though HDFS changes internal APIs, public interfacing would remains same. So, Hbase/Other dependent users need not end up with reflections for every compatibility change.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13244731" author="stack" created="Mon, 2 Apr 2012 22:15:41 +0000"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;What is the final result of this voting?&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It passed.  For a while it wavered but then Mikhail said that his team would be fine if 1.0.0 became the baseline for 0.96.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;We should not access any non exposed APIs from HDFS at least from this version. &lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;That&apos;d be nice.  Agree would be sweet if we didn&apos;t have to do reflection at all going forward.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13245345" author="jmhsieh" created="Tue, 3 Apr 2012 14:18:22 +0000"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;That&apos;d be nice. Agree would be sweet if we didn&apos;t have to do reflection at all going forward.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Or at least to remove reflection require for pre-hadoop 1.0.0.  We will probably eventually need it again for hadoop 0.23 hdfs...&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13459172" author="stack" created="Wed, 19 Sep 2012 22:35:48 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Addition to doc. that says Hadoop 1.0.x required for 0.96 citing the discussion on mailing list.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13459173" author="stack" created="Wed, 19 Sep 2012 22:36:06 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Committed to trunk.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
